Deputy President William Ruto will on Sunday take his campaigns to Meru county, as he continues his tour of the Eastern region. Ruto will lead his Kenya Kwanza coalition partners in drumming up support for his presidential bid. The second in command will first attend a church service in Maua Catholic Church before making stopovers inÂ Kiutine Market in Igembe Central constituency, Igembe North, Kionyo Market and Ex-Lewa Market in Buuri constituency. During the stopovers, the DP will address residents as well as sell his Bottom-up economic agenda as he seeks their votes in the August 9 polls. ODM leader Raila Odinga will also continue his tour of the coast that began in Kilifi county on Saturday. Raila will hold rallies in Mazeras, Miritini and Tononoka grounds in Mombasa where he will sell his plans for the country if elected president in August. The former PM is on a four-day tour of the Coast region.